  "text": "To ensure that CTC clusters do not dissociate, the chip is optimized to handle cellular aggregates with flow speeds (and therefore shear forces) well below those found in human capillaries. The peak flow speed of ~70 µm/s at the bifurcation (Fig. 1d) is much lower than that of existing microfluidic and filter-based CTC isolation technologies [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Yet the chip can interrogate clinical blood specimens at a rate of 2.5 ml/h owing to its highly parallel architecture (Fig. 1c) .",
